{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-blog-post-js","path":"/blog/code-block-highlights-for-Gatsby-ReactJS-blogs/","webpackCompilationHash":"453333408ad0efa940a5","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"html":"<p>If you are using Gatsby as static website or blog, porbably you are a developer. In that case, you will need code syntax highlightings to the code blocks. As usual Gatsby provide us a easy way to achieve it into oir markdown.</p>\n<h3>Run the next command:</h3>\n<p><em>npm install --save gatsby-remark-prismjs prismjs</em></p>\n<p>Once installed, open your gatsby-config.js file and add:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"javascript\"><pre style=\"counter-reset: linenumber NaN\" class=\"language-javascript line-numbers\"><code class=\"language-javascript\">plugins<span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">[</span>\n  <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n    resolve<span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> <span class=\"token template-string\"><span class=\"token template-punctuation string\">`</span><span class=\"token string\">gatsby-transformer-remark</span><span class=\"token template-punctuation string\">`</span></span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n    options<span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n      plugins<span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">[</span>\n        <span class=\"token template-string\"><span class=\"token template-punctuation string\">`</span><span class=\"token string\">gatsby-remark-prismjs</span><span class=\"token template-punctuation string\">`</span></span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n      <span class=\"token punctuation\">]</span>\n    <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n  <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">]</span></code><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"line-numbers-rows\" style=\"white-space: normal; width: auto; left: 0;\"><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span></span></pre></div>\n<p>Note: probably you was using already <code class=\"language-text\">gatsby-transformer-remark</code> so, just swap this line for those.</p>\n<p>Next, open gatsbybrowser.js_ and add:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"css\"><pre style=\"counter-reset: linenumber NaN\" class=\"language-css line-numbers\"><code class=\"language-css\"><span class=\"token function\">require</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token string\">\"prismjs/themes/prism-solarizedlight.css\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token function\">require</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token string\">\"prismjs/plugins/line-numbers/prism-line-numbers.css\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span></code><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"line-numbers-rows\" style=\"white-space: normal; width: auto; left: 0;\"><span></span><span></span></span></pre></div>\n<p>To use in markdown, add three followed by language name as:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"text\"><pre style=\"counter-reset: linenumber NaN\" class=\"language-text line-numbers\"><code class=\"language-text\">```javascript\nplugins: [\n  {\n    resolve: `gatsby-transformer-remark`undefined\n    options: {\n      plugins: [\n        `gatsby-remark-prismjs`undefined\n      ]\n    }\n  }\n]```</code><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"line-numbers-rows\" style=\"white-space: normal; width: auto; left: 0;\"><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span></span></pre></div>\n<p>That's all! Remember markdown syntax: add a &#x3C;pre> tag is done by adding four empty spaces.</p>\n<p>And, of course, check official plugin documentation <a href=\"https://www.gatsbyjs.org/packages/gatsby-remark-prismjs/\">here</a>.</p>","frontmatter":{"title":"Code block highlights for Gatsby ReactJS blogs","subtitle":"Syntax highlighting to the code blocks","date":"08 May, 2019","image":"/blog/code-highlight.png","tags":["javascript","markdown","gatsby"]}}},"pageContext":{"isCreatedByStatefulCreatePages":false,"slug":"/blog/code-block-highlights-for-Gatsby-ReactJS-blogs/"}}}